SECTION 1 — WHAT THIS LICENSE COVERS
─────────────────────────────────────
This MIT License applies to all source code, configuration files, scripts,
documentation, assets, and associated materials that form the finSight-AI
project, including but not limited to:

  • Backend Python source code (agents, orchestrators, pipelines, routes,
    data loaders, feature stores, evaluation modules, explainability modules,
    audit trail systems, and database interfaces)

  • Frontend source code (React/JSX components, Tailwind CSS styling,
    Vite build configuration, Firebase integration, and all associated assets)

  • Machine learning training pipelines, model configuration files, and
    synthetic data generation utilities

  • Infrastructure files including Dockerfiles, docker-compose configurations,
    CI/CD definitions, and deployment manifests (render.yaml)

  • Documentation files including README.md, PROJECT_DOCUMENTATION.md,
    SYSTEM_ARCHITECTURE.md, STARTUP.md, and all other Markdown documents

  • Test suites, notebooks, and utility scripts included in the repository

